title: The Doings of Raffles Haw
creator: Sir Arthur Conan Doyle
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Doings of Raffles Haw, by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle. Read by Patrick Wells. The people of the small town of Tamfield are not used to exciting things happening. When millionaire Raffles Haw moves to town, rumors spread like wildfire about him. The advent of Mr. Haw, however, changes the town, and particularly the lives of the McIntyre family, in ways no one could ever have guessed. (summary by Patrick Wells) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (99MB)
